FAIL_TO_PASS: when call error() then throw CommanderError
when custom processing for argument throws InvalidArgumentError then catch CommanderError
when option argument not in choices then throw CommanderError
when executableSubcommand succeeds then call exitOverride
when specify excess argument then throw CommanderError
when specify option without required value then throw CommanderError
when executable subcommand and no command specified then throw CommanderError
when has conflicting option then throw CommanderError
when command has exitOverride and executable subcommand fails then program exit code is subcommand exit code
when specify program without required argument and no action handler then throw CommanderError
when specify command without required argument then throw CommanderError
when custom processing for option throws InvalidArgumentError then catch CommanderError
when specify unknown command then throw CommanderError
when specify command with excess argument then throw CommanderError
when specify unknown program option then throw CommanderError
when command argument not in choices then throw CommanderError
when mandatory program option missing then throw CommanderError
